metadata.title: RESEARCH: PowerShell Timestomping Script (script block)
metadata.description:
A script block event associated with the use of PowerShell to modify file timestamps has been identified. This may indicate that a threat actor is attempting to remove evidence.

Example
> powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -WindowStyle Minimized -Command $FileItem = Get-Item """C:\Users\admin\notes.txt""" ; $FileItem.CreationTime = """02/26/2019 22:00:27""" ; $FileItem.LastWriteTime = """09/15/2018 07:28:25""" ; $FileItem.LastAccessTime = """03/01/2019 17:23:58""""
